# Project: Save a Stray V2

## Tech Stack & Architecture
- Language: Kotlin
- UI Framework: Jetpack Compose (Strictly use Compose, do not use old XML layouts)
- Architecture: MVVM (Model-View-ViewModel)
- Backend & Database: Firebase Authentication and Cloud Firestore
- Networking: Retrofit (Set up base API interfaces for a future ML Matching Engine)

## Database Schema (Firestore)
1. **Users Collection**
   - Fields: uid (String), email (String), role (Enum: ADOPTER, INDIVIDUAL, SHELTER), location (GeoPoint), name/orgName (String)
2. **Pets Collection**
   - Fields: petId (String), ownerId (String - ref to Users), name (String), breed (String), location (GeoPoint), vaccinationStatus (Boolean), personalityTraits (List<String>), status (Enum: AVAILABLE, PENDING, ADOPTED)

## Agent Operational Rules
- Never auto-execute terminal commands without user permission.
- Prioritize clean, modular composables for the UI. 
- When handling user registration, branch the UI flow immediately based on the selected user role.
- Always implement clean separation of concerns using the MVVM pattern.